            <abstract>
                <p>In the catalogue description of <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr13"/>, Strelcyn
                    identifies one miracle of the healing of a man with paralyzed feet. It seems
                    likely that this corresponds to three very short miracles of the edition
                    (<bibl><ptr target="bm:Colin2010MadhaninaEgzi"/><citedRange unit="page">562</citedRange></bibl>):
                1. the healing of a man with paralyzed feet, 2. the resuscitation of a little boy
                and 3. another healing of a man with a limp.
                </p>
